The federal government in collaboration with the United Nations Development Program (UNDP) is set to launch the 2018 human development report. In a statement signed by the communication specialist, the 2018 Human Development Report highlights the human development issues in North-East Nigeria and explores avenues for expanding people’s choices and freedoms in the crisis region. Achim Steiner, UNDP Administrator and Mark Lowcock, Emergency Relief Coordinator  who are on a visit to Nigeria and Chad on a mission to highlight, support joint humanitarian and development efforts in these countries, are expected to be present at the event. They are also expected to speak on stakeholders efforts to respond to the devastating consequences of the ongoing violence in north-eastern Nigeria, while seeking to promote durable solutions for the affected communities. Zainab Ahmed, Minister of Finance, and Udoma Udo Udoma, Minister of Budget and National Planning will join visiting UNDP Administrator Achim Steiner and Humanitarian Chief, Mark Lowcock at the dinner to launch the National Human Development 2018, tonight in Abuja. 